{"questionId":"9337","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span> is defined by&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = {{\\text{e}}^{{\\text{sin}}\\,x}}\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>sin</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that the coefficient of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{x^3}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> in the Maclaurin series for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> is zero.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em><strong>METHOD 1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempting to differentiate&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f''\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <msup>\n    <mi>f</mi>\n    <mo>″</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f'''\\left( x \\right) = \\left( {{\\text{cos}}\\,x} \\right){{\\text{e}}^{{\\text{sin}}\\,x}}\\left( {{\\text{co}}{{\\text{s}}^2}\\,x - {\\text{sin}}\\,x} \\right) - \\left( {{\\text{cos}}\\,x} \\right){{\\text{e}}^{{\\text{sin}}\\,x}}\\left( {2\\,{\\text{sin}}\\,x + 1} \\right)\">\n  <msup>\n    <mi>f</mi>\n    <mo>‴</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>cos</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>sin</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>co</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>s</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>sin</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>cos</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>sin</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>sin</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A2</strong></em></p>\n<p>substituting <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 0\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span> into <strong>their</strong> <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f'''\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <msup>\n    <mi>f</mi>\n    <mo>‴</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f'''\\left( 0 \\right) = 1\\left( {1 - 0} \\right) - 1\\left( {0 + 1} \\right) = 0\">\n  <msup>\n    <mi>f</mi>\n    <mo>‴</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>so&nbsp;the coefficient of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{x^3}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> in the Maclaurin series for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> is zero&nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><em>METHOD 2</em></strong></p>\n<p>substituting <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{{\\text{sin}}\\,x}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>sin</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> into the Maclaurin series for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{{\\text{e}}^x}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{{\\text{e}}^{{\\text{sin}}\\,x}} = 1 + {\\text{sin}}\\,x + \\frac{{{\\text{si}}{{\\text{n}}^2}\\,x}}{{2{\\text{!}}}} + \\frac{{{\\text{si}}{{\\text{n}}^3}\\,x}}{{3{\\text{!}}}} +&nbsp; \\ldots \">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>sin</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>si</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>n</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>!</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>si</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>n</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>!</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mo>…</mo>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>substituting Maclaurin series for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{{\\text{sin}}\\,x}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>sin</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{{\\text{e}}^{{\\text{sin}}\\,x}} = 1 + \\left( {x - \\frac{{{x^3}}}{{3{\\text{!}}}} +&nbsp; \\ldots } \\right) + \\frac{{{{\\left( {x - \\frac{{{x^3}}}{{3{\\text{!}}}} +&nbsp; \\ldots } \\right)}^2}}}{{2{\\text{!}}}} + \\frac{{{{\\left( {x - \\frac{{{x^3}}}{{3{\\text{!}}}} +&nbsp; \\ldots } \\right)}^3}}}{{3{\\text{!}}}} +&nbsp; \\ldots \">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>sin</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>x</mi>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>!</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mo>…</mo>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>(</mo>\n              <mrow>\n                <mi>x</mi>\n                <mo>−</mo>\n                <mfrac>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mrow>\n                      <msup>\n                        <mi>x</mi>\n                        <mn>3</mn>\n                      </msup>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mn>3</mn>\n                    <mrow>\n                      <mtext>!</mtext>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mfrac>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <mo>…</mo>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo>)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>!</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>(</mo>\n              <mrow>\n                <mi>x</mi>\n                <mo>−</mo>\n                <mfrac>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mrow>\n                      <msup>\n                        <mi>x</mi>\n                        <mn>3</mn>\n                      </msup>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mn>3</mn>\n                    <mrow>\n                      <mtext>!</mtext>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mfrac>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <mo>…</mo>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo>)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>!</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mo>…</mo>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>coefficient of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{x^3}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> is&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - \\frac{1}{{3{\\text{!}}}} + \\frac{1}{{3{\\text{!}}}} = 0\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>!</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>!</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>so&nbsp;the coefficient of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{x^3}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> in the Maclaurin series for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> is zero&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9337","referenceCode":"SPM.1.AHL.TZ0.12b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that the coefficient of x 3 in the Maclaurin series for f ( x ) is zero.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.19—Maclaurin series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}